# Login Form Testing Scenarios

| Test Case ID | Test Case Description                                      | Pre-Condition                    | Steps                                                                                                                                                                   | Expected Result                                                                                                      |
|--------------|------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| TC001        | Verify Login with valid credentials                        | User is on the login page        | 1. Navigate to login page<br>2. Enter valid email and password<br>3. Click on "Login" button                                                                            | User should be redirected to the dashboard/homepage.                                                                 |
| TC002        | Verify Login with invalid credentials                      | User is on the login page        | 1. Navigate to login page<br>2. Enter an invalid email and password<br>3. Click on "Login" button                                                                       | An error message like “Invalid username or password” should be displayed.                                             |
| TC003        | Verify Login with blank username and password              | User is on the login page        | 1. Navigate to login page<br>2. Leave the email and password fields blank<br>3. Click on "Login" button                                                                 | A validation message like “Please enter your email and password” should be displayed.                                 |
| TC004        | Verify Login when password is left blank                   | User is on the login page        | 1. Navigate to login page<br>2. Enter valid email<br>3. Leave password blank<br>4. Click on "Login" button                                                              | A validation message like “Password is required” should be displayed.                                                |
| TC005        | Verify Login when email format is incorrect                | User is on the login page        | 1. Navigate to login page<br>2. Enter invalid email format (e.g., "abc@com")<br>3. Enter valid password<br>4. Click "Login" button                                      | A validation message like “Please enter a valid email address” should be displayed.                                   |
| TC006        | Verify "Forgot Password" link functionality                | User is on the login page        | 1. Navigate to login page<br>2. Click on the "Forgot Password" link                                                                                                     | The user should be redirected to the password recovery page.                                                         |
| TC007        | Verify that user cannot log in after multiple failed attempts | User has failed login attempts | 1. Attempt to login with invalid credentials multiple times (e.g., 5 times)<br>2. Observe the system's behavior                                                         | The system should lock the account after the defined number of failed attempts, or show a CAPTCHA for verification.   |
| TC008        | Verify "Remember Me" functionality                         | User is on the login page        | 1. Navigate to login page<br>2. Enter valid email and password<br>3. Select the "Remember Me" checkbox<br>4. Click on "Login" button                                     | The system should remember the user’s credentials for the next session.                                               |
| TC009        | Verify Login redirects to correct page after login         | User is on the login page with redirection URL | 1. Try accessing a restricted page directly without logging in (e.g., "/user/orders")<br>2. Perform login when prompted<br>3. Observe the redirection behavior          | After successful login, the user should be redirected to the originally requested page.                               |
